<br>
I'm sick to death of seeing people post things like 'No caster should ever have gate memmed if they're in a group'  and 'A caster should never gate out of a battle' blah blah blah.<br>
<br>
What a totally ridiculous sentiment.  If caster can gate out of a group wipeout situation, then by all means they should do so!  If you're going to end up at your bind point one way or the other, I'd prefer it to be dressed and buffed.<br>
<br>
Unnecessary deaths are a drain on the group.  It's one extra corpse to retrieve and resurrect, one more body to heal up, one more person to be buffed.  One more peridot down the drain.  I don't begrudge replacing symbol buffs when a group wipes - don't get me wrong - but I really do begrudge it when someone could have escaped and didn't because for one reason or another, they weren't 'allowed' to Gate.<br>
<br>
I fail to see why anyone who can gate should be 'forced' to stay and die.  At the very least they should feel that they have the right to go to safety if their group is being shredded.<br>
<br>
I totally understand that not everyone has room in their spell lineup to include gate - depending on where and what you're fighting, it may not be practical to have it there.  I also understand that you can't always channel it successfully.  This isn't in any way aimed at anyone who would-if-they-could.<br>
<br>
This is about selfish melees who think they can lay down the law and say that because they can't gate, nobody else can either.<br>
<br>
It's also about casters who insist that it is more noble to die with your group than to escape to safety - despite the fact that they're not the ones stuck with the rez-heal-buff cycle. <br>
<br>
(And yes, I have been in situations before where the casters could have gated, and in fact were told to escape when it was obvious the situation would turn to a wipeout, and instead chose to stay with an &quot;I shall die in your defence!&quot; attitude.  Very noble, very dramatic.   Not really very *nice* though, if you see what I'm saying.)<br>
<br>
Time to realise that they're call 'casters' for a reason.  They cast spells.  Spells to draw in prey, spells to damage it, and spells to escape it.  Despite what melees seem to think, Gate is not there merely to provide easy access to a bank.  <br>
<br>
Sometimes gating out of a situation is not only the most logical thing to do, it can also be the most responsible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khiadra>Khiadra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/22/03 12:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3916.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Casters who gate out of battles ...</span><hr size=1> Oh, my my.  I somehow ended up in OOC. <br>
