<br>
It is lame if someone gates at the first hint of trouble.  Even more lame if you abandon the group (ala Shadowglade).  That is what you are mostly detecting in terms of hostility.  However, if everyone knows that it is a hopeless cause, then by all means gate.  In my groups, I will often tell the casters to gate and try to hold off the mobs as long as I can before I have to feign.  In those situations, as a monk, I am often the only person that survives wipes and I can tell you that doing a cr in a dungeon with two or three geared folks as opposed to just me is *much* easier.<br>
<br>
