<br>
I dont mind if a wizard or druid evacced, that means everyone made it out.  Sometimes it's better safe than sorry.<br>
<br>
I'm not against turning tail and making for the zone or gating out, when the situation asks for it.  But when the group might be able to make it and THEN you gate out without a word being said.... that's wrong.<br>
<br>
Heck, I used to yell at casters in Karnor's when we called run and they'd dawdle at the zoneline... when I say &quot;run&quot; I mean RUN!  Sitting at zoneline means the dutiful tank will wait til the casters zone out (because a caster with 4 things beating on him gets stunned too much to move.  And the tank has 4+ things on him/her and when the tank zones out, they'll migrate to anyone else standing at the zoneline)... I know the cleric is trying to get a heal off, but just zone, please... that lets me get out that much faster.<br>
