<br>
In any case, if the pull is sooooooooooo bad that the puller is creating an instant train, he shouldn't bring it back to the party - the puller should die before he returns. That's proper. Gating is ok.  <br>
<br>
HYPOTHETICAL: But the reason you gate out is because the puller brings two back, and the enchanter dies, you gate out, leaving your party to die. That sucks. You're a coward. The bard is sitting there backup mezzing, and everyone would've survived. And you gated your sorry cleric ass out. <br>
<br>
This hypothetical situation is based on the actions of a group I was in recently, that succor'd out after the enchanter died. If we didn't have someone who could succor, we would've stayed and faught. If the cleric had gated out, we all would've died. <br>
<br>
